  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis in centrifugal blood pumps under ventricular assist device operating conditions. The CFD hemolysis model targets the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry and was evaluated against in-vitro hemolysis index measurements. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across 500 parameter draws. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are addressed; seven were fully assessed and six were scoped out due to data availability constraints at Model Risk Level 5. The overall credibility assessment concludes that the model is adequate for the intended comparative ranking of design variants. No structured Context of Use object is provided under the Minimal profile; intended-use scope is conveyed through this narrative only.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-vad-001",
